41:07.541 --> 41:08.833
Hmm.

41:12.208 --> 41:14.458
Heh.

42:57.625 --> 42:58.917
Get... no.

43:00.249 --> 43:02.917
No!

43:30.999 --> 43:32.750
- Good God, no.

43:32.833 --> 43:35.124
He's beginning to realize it.

43:35.208 --> 43:37.208
♪ ♪

43:37.291 --> 43:39.375
- Beginning to realize what?

43:42.667 --> 43:43.917
- That he has power.

43:43.999 --> 43:46.083
- ♪ Hands too burnt ♪

43:49.833 --> 43:55.083
- ♪ Ain't got an honest
feeling in my bones ♪

43:55.166 --> 43:57.958
♪ Felt like a fever ♪

43:58.041 --> 44:00.625
♪ Came on like a storm ♪

44:00.708 --> 44:01.958
♪ But what I felt ♪

44:02.041 --> 44:04.917
♪ It can't be helped no more ♪

44:04.999 --> 44:06.291
♪ ♪

44:06.375 --> 44:08.750
♪ Get up, up, up, up,
up, up, up ♪

44:08.833 --> 44:09.833
♪ If you want ♪

44:29.416 --> 44:33.249
♪ ♪

44:41.750 --> 44:44.041
- ♪ Won't leave you cold ♪

44:44.124 --> 44:45.833
♪ ♪

44:45.917 --> 44:47.999
♪ I'm a believer ♪

44:48.083 --> 44:49.583
♪ My word's as good as gold ♪

44:55.708 --> 44:58.625
Whoo!

45:51.166 --> 45:52.875
Where is your...

45:58.041 --> 46:01.958
- Mother, would you please
bring me some Easter cake?

46:02.041 --> 46:05.166
The one made by Alemagna.

46:08.541 --> 46:12.792
- Holy Father, Easter cake
is only made at Easter time.

46:13.958 --> 46:15.333
That's months away.

46:16.667 --> 46:18.541
- I don't care.

46:18.625 --> 46:20.958
You would to do well
to get me some.

46:21.041 --> 46:24.124
Otherwise, I will get upset,

46:24.208 --> 46:28.833
and it's not good
if the pope gets upset.

46:29.999 --> 46:31.583
Hmm?

46:44.541 --> 46:47.208
What happened
to the Venus of Willendorf?

46:48.041 --> 46:50.958
- I imagined you would want
to sell it, Holy Father,

46:51.041 --> 46:53.750
and donate the proceeds
to the poor,

46:53.833 --> 46:58.208
so I sent it to London
to be auctioned at Christie's.

46:58.291 --> 47:02.625
- And were you sorry
to part with her?

47:02.708 --> 47:05.333
- Attachment to material things
is an emotion

47:05.416 --> 47:09.291
that does not pertain to
the Vatican secretary of state.

47:09.375 --> 47:11.041
- Nor to the pope.

47:11.124 --> 47:14.583
In fact, we will divest
ourselves of everything.

47:14.667 --> 47:16.999
- Even the refugees,
Holy Father?

47:17.083 --> 47:19.166
- No.

47:19.249 --> 47:20.875
They will stay.

47:23.041 --> 47:26.500
It was a brilliant move
on my part,

47:26.583 --> 47:29.375
a charitable media triumph.

47:29.458 --> 47:33.458
My papacy will be one long,

47:33.541 --> 47:38.333
luxurious manifestation
of poverty.

47:38.416 --> 47:40.999
- Which has us all worried,
Holy Father.

47:41.083 --> 47:43.124
- Yes, I can imagine.

47:43.208 --> 47:45.166
The time of privilege is over,

47:45.249 --> 47:48.625
but I am not afraid
of your reactions, Voiello,

47:48.708 --> 47:50.458
or that of the Curia.

47:50.541 --> 47:52.166
And do you know why?

47:52.249 --> 47:55.500
Because the people and the press

47:55.583 --> 47:57.291
are all on my side,

47:57.375 --> 47:59.166
the leftist press in particular.

47:59.249 --> 48:00.625
- Which is exactly why

48:00.708 --> 48:03.375
I invite you to be prudent,
Holy Father.

48:03.458 --> 48:06.583
The leftist press
never gets anything right.

48:06.667 --> 48:10.291
They have even lost ground
in nursing homes.

48:11.291 --> 48:13.375
- By the way,

48:13.458 --> 48:16.667
as soon as possible,
we must consider the selection

48:16.750 --> 48:18.999
of the new secretary of state.

48:19.083 --> 48:22.041
- May I have a word with you
in private, Holy Father?

48:22.124 --> 48:24.750
- Oh, you may speak with me
in public, Voiello.

48:24.833 --> 48:26.875
I have no secrets.

48:26.958 --> 48:28.416
- But I do, Holy Father.

48:36.291 --> 48:38.833
- No, no, no.
What are you doing here?

48:38.917 --> 48:40.875
- It's full, full, full, full,
full, full, full.

48:42.999 --> 48:47.208
- We mistakenly thought
we could have some lunch here.

48:47.291 --> 48:52.375
- You have to go
to the Sistine Chapel... now.

48:52.458 --> 48:57.166
Francis II is going to address
his brother cardinals.

49:06.375 --> 49:07.999
- It's full, full, full,
full, full.

49:13.124 --> 49:16.083
It's full, full, full,
full, full.

49:16.166 --> 49:17.375
It's full.

49:33.208 --> 49:34.208
Hmm.

49:39.999 --> 49:42.333
Brother cardinals...

49:46.208 --> 49:47.541
Thank you.

49:48.750 --> 49:51.833
Thank you for having placed

49:51.917 --> 49:55.833
a poor, ignorant,

49:55.917 --> 49:59.333
awkward monk
on the papal throne.

50:01.917 --> 50:04.083
I would like
to address you today,

50:04.166 --> 50:06.750
but who am I to speak to you?

50:08.124 --> 50:09.458
I'm just a poor man.

50:10.792 --> 50:14.625
Far better that I speak to you
in the words of the saint

50:14.708 --> 50:17.124
who, as of today,

50:17.208 --> 50:20.416
shall be an inspiration
to us all.

50:26.416 --> 50:28.416
- It's not looking good.

50:30.583 --> 50:34.041
- From the Testament
of Saint Francis.

50:35.750 --> 50:39.500
"And those who came to embrace
this life

50:39.583 --> 50:43.875
"gave as much as they could
to the poor.

50:43.958 --> 50:47.833
"They were content
with a single tunic,

50:47.917 --> 50:52.458
patched within and without
at will."

50:53.833 --> 50:57.249
Or... or... or...

50:57.333 --> 50:58.500
- Who's he?

51:02.416 --> 51:04.041
- The new pope.

51:04.124 --> 51:05.375
- Or this,

51:05.458 --> 51:07.917
the last wishes to Saint Clare.

51:09.958 --> 51:12.708
"And I counsel you

51:12.792 --> 51:14.917
"to live always in this

51:14.999 --> 51:20.458
most holy life of poverty."

51:26.667 --> 51:30.249
My dear brethren cardinals,

51:30.333 --> 51:33.458
starting today, we will all live

51:33.541 --> 51:36.999
according to the rules
of Saint Francis.

51:38.166 --> 51:41.833
Poverty will be our uniform.

51:43.208 --> 51:46.375
And so as we intone together

51:46.458 --> 51:49.249
the "Canticle of Creatures,"

51:49.333 --> 51:52.375
some friars will move among you,

51:52.458 --> 51:57.083
inviting you to place
your gold crosses

51:57.166 --> 52:01.249
and your precious
bejeweled rings

52:01.333 --> 52:02.875
in the baskets.

52:02.958 --> 52:08.083
All your finery will be sold...

52:08.166 --> 52:11.166
the proceeds given to the poor.
- Stand up. Up, up.

52:11.249 --> 52:12.124
Stand up.

52:12.208 --> 52:14.999
- I know, I know you will
obey me in this,

52:15.083 --> 52:18.833
that you will not cause
your pope to become upset.

52:18.917 --> 52:20.500
Hmm?

52:20.583 --> 52:24.999
In exchange, I will embrace

52:25.083 --> 52:27.166
each of you.

