57:49.375 --> 57:51.792
- He has taken control
of the vault.

57:51.875 --> 57:55.124
He plans to give it all away,

57:55.208 --> 57:57.375
all the money,
all the gold to the poor,

57:57.458 --> 57:59.333
the secret files to the press.

57:59.416 --> 58:01.333
We will all end up in jail.

58:01.416 --> 58:03.792
- He has heard the word of God

58:03.875 --> 58:06.750
and decided to follow literally.

58:06.833 --> 58:08.333
- God was emotional.

58:08.416 --> 58:11.291
- But we are expected to be
farsighted.

58:11.375 --> 58:13.958
- Half of the cardinals
vote for you,

58:14.041 --> 58:16.249
the other half for me.

58:16.333 --> 58:19.291
Neither one of us
will ever become pope.

58:19.375 --> 58:20.833
- I know.

58:20.917 --> 58:23.999
We have to find a third choice.

58:24.083 --> 58:25.291
- Who do you have in mind?

58:25.375 --> 58:27.500
- The person who got
the most votes

58:27.583 --> 58:29.625
after you and me.

58:31.750 --> 58:33.166
- Sir John Brannox?

58:33.249 --> 58:37.208
- Yes, him, the great advocate
for the middle way.

58:37.291 --> 58:39.208
- I have never even met him.

58:39.291 --> 58:43.375
- You'll like him,
a compelling individual.

58:43.458 --> 58:45.291
There is only one problem.

58:45.375 --> 58:48.708
It will not be easy
to convince him to accept,

58:48.792 --> 58:53.667
but you, Voiello,
are enormously persuasive.

58:53.750 --> 58:54.999
Oh, yes.

58:55.083 --> 58:58.208
Why is it that you and I
have never been able

58:58.291 --> 59:00.375
to tolerate each other?

59:00.458 --> 59:02.875
- We are too different.

59:06.291 --> 59:09.750
- But there is an obstacle
between our intention

59:09.833 --> 59:14.375
and Brannox becoming pope:
Francis II.

59:14.458 --> 59:16.875
How shall we proceed?

59:16.958 --> 59:20.458
- With the power of prayer
and good will.

